// GL NOTES

// NOTE 1:

    ## Render part of VBO with glDrawElements():

    The fourth argument specifies a pointer offset to the data in bytes.
    Since the index buffer is an integer, the offset must be multiplied by 4.
    Also, since the buffer is grouped as Vec3, the offset must be a multiple of 3.

    Example ->

        // draw first half
        glDrawElements(*, getDivisibleBy3(getVertexCount()/2), *, 0);
        // draw second half
        glDrawElements(*, getVertexCount(), *, getDivisibleBy3(getVertexCount()/2)*4);

    ## MTL File cheat sheet

        Color reflectivity (VEC3):
        - ambient (Ka, map_Ka) -> (1-tex.alpha) * material.ambient + tex.alpha * tex.ambient;
        - diffuse (Kd, map_Kd) -> (1-tex.alpha) * material.diffuse + tex.alpha * tex.diffuse;
        - specular (Ks, map_Ks) -> (1-tex.alpha) * material.specular + tex.alpha * tex.specular;

        Other values (f):
        - specular exponent (Ns) (0-1000f)
        - illumination (illum) (0-2f)